verbose_text: RP105 overexpression with adenovirus vectors reduced serum myocardial enzyme (CK-MB and LDH) activities, decreased myocardial infarct size and mitigated inflammatory factors IFN-beta and TNF-alpha during MIRI, and TLR4 / TRIF signal pathway relative proteins and mRNAs (TRIF, TBK-1, IRF3 and p-IRF3) were repressed with a low transcriptional activity of IRF3.
